PN,41804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1777385513
OL,3,CMother publishes moving memoir
OL,4,Cfollowing accident that claimed
OL,5,Cdaughter's life
OL,7,FShe credits her awakening to her Uncle
OL,8,FAsh, who sat by her bedside reading
OL,9,Fthe same Ninja Turtle stories he had
OL,10,Ftold her as a child.
OL,12,FUpon waking, Dani was faced with
OL,13,Flosing her daughter and the news that
OL,14,Fshe would never walk again.
OL,16,F"I think I kind of went numb," Dani
OL,17,Fsaid. "I think my brain injury
OL,18,Fprotected me from a lot of that
OL,19,Fbecause it wouldn't allow me to
OL,20,Fprocess things.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,419,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1777385513
OL,3,CMother publishes moving memoir
OL,4,Cfollowing accident that claimed
OL,5,Cdaughter's life
OL,7,F"My brain injury is invisible... but
OL,8,Fto those who know me, it's very
OL,9,Fprominent."
OL,11,FDuring a nine-month stay at the spinal
OL,12,Funit in Salisbury, Dani began writing.
OL,14,FShe found that while doctors could
OL,15,Fprovide medical facts, they couldn't
OL,16,Fanswer the personal questions about
OL,17,Fliving with paralysis.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
